  "prompt": "What are some visible signs of pregnancy?",
  "response": "Visible signs of pregnancy can vary from woman to woman, but some common signs include:\n\n1. Enlarged and tender breasts: Early in pregnancy, a woman\u2019s breasts may become larger, more sensitive, and tender to the touch.\n\n2. A missed period: This is often the first sign that a woman may be pregnant, especially if she has a regular menstrual cycle.\n\n3. Nausea and vomiting: Commonly known as morning sickness, this can occur at any time of the day and may start as early as two weeks after conception.\n\n4. Increased urination: Pregnant women often need to urinate more frequently due to hormonal changes and increased blood flow to the kidneys.\n\n5. Fatigue: Feeling tired and exhausted is common in early pregnancy due to increased levels of the hormone progesterone.\n\n6. Weight gain: As the pregnancy progresses, weight gain is expected and normal. Most women gain between 25-35 pounds during pregnancy.\n\n7. Changes in skin: Hormonal changes during pregnancy can cause the skin to become darker in certain areas, such as the nipples, and can also cause acne or melasma, a condition that causes dark patches on the face.\n\n8. A growing belly: As the baby grows, the uterus expands, and the belly will become more prominent. This usually becomes noticeable around the second trimester.\n\nIt is worth mentioning that although these indicators may imply pregnancy, they are not absolute proof. To confirm pregnancy, one should take a pregnancy test and consult a healthcare provider.",
